    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-24T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="791"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d791">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6359 Antimony/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-24T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 24, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>138. Your despatch No. 3503 of April 12 in regard to the Hunan Antimony
                    Syndicate. Although your despatch under reference indicates clearly the views of
                    the Chinese Government and, to a lesser degree, the views of the British and
                    Japanese Legations in regard to the syndicate, it does not include either the
                    views or recommendations of the American Legation as to possible future
                    action.</p>
                <p>Department, before giving further consideration to this subject in the light of
                    the note addressed to the Legation by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs under date
                    April 4,<note n="78" xml:id="d791fn78">Not printed.</note> desires to receive,
                    either by radio or by mail, a statement of your views and recommendations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
